Edition:
Quote: And we do hereby declare, that from henceforth the said islands shall be known and designated as the colony of New Zealand, and the principal islands, heretofore known as or commonly called the `Northern Island', the `Middle Island', and `Stewart's Island', shall henceforth be designated and known respectively as `New Ulster', `New Munster', and `New Leinster'. ...Provided always, that nothing in these our letters patent contained shall affect ... the rights of any aboriginal natives of the said colony of New Zealand to the actual occupation or enjoyment in their own persons, or in the persons of their descendants, of any lands in the said colony now actually occupied or enjoyed by such natives.
Notes: 1840 Nov 16 Charter for Erecting the Colony of NZ in 1949 Rutherford ed. Select Documents 8

